business_definition: Main export record structure containing all record types for branch migration (Total Record Length: 500 bytes)
Record type identifier to distinguish between different export record structures
Full timestamp of when the export record was created
Parsed timestamp structure (REDEFINES EXPORT-TIMESTAMP)
Date portion of the export timestamp
Separator character between date and time components
Time portion of the export timestamp
Sequential number for ordering export records (USAGE COMP)
Branch identifier for the originating branch location
Geographic region code for the branch
Variable data area containing different record type structures
Customer information record structure (REDEFINES EXPORT-RECORD-DATA)
Unique customer identifier (USAGE COMP)
Customer's first name
Customer's middle name
Customer's last name
Customer address lines group (OCCURS 3 TIMES)
Individual address line for customer mailing address
Two-character state code for customer address
Three-character country code for customer address
Postal zip code for customer address
Customer phone numbers group (OCCURS 2 TIMES)
Individual phone number for customer contact
Customer's Social Security Number
Government-issued identification number for customer
Customer's date of birth in YYYY-MM-DD format
Electronic Funds Transfer account identifier
Primary cardholder indicator flag
Customer's FICO credit score (USAGE COMP-3)
Reserved placeholder field used for data structure alignment, padding, or holding constant values
Account information record structure (REDEFINES EXPORT-RECORD-DATA)
Unique account identifier
Account active status indicator
Current account balance (USAGE COMP-3)
Maximum credit limit for the account
Cash advance credit limit (USAGE COMP-3)
Date when the account was opened
Account expiration date
Date when the account was reissued
Current cycle credit amount
Current cycle debit amount (USAGE COMP)
Postal zip code for account billing address
Account group identifier for related accounts
Reserved placeholder field used for data structure alignment, padding, or holding constant values
Transaction information record structure (REDEFINES EXPORT-RECORD-DATA)
Unique transaction identifier
Transaction type code
Transaction category code
Source system or channel of the transaction
Detailed description of the transaction
Transaction amount (USAGE COMP-3)
Unique merchant identifier (USAGE COMP)
Name of the merchant where transaction occurred
City location of the merchant
Postal zip code of the merchant location
Card number used for the transaction
Original timestamp when transaction was initiated
Processing timestamp when transaction was completed
Reserved placeholder field used for data structure alignment, padding, or holding constant values
Card cross-reference record structure linking cards to customers and accounts (REDEFINES EXPORT-RECORD-DATA)
Card number in cross-reference relationship
Customer identifier in cross-reference relationship
Account identifier in cross-reference relationship (USAGE COMP)
Reserved placeholder field used for data structure alignment, padding, or holding constant values
Card information record structure (REDEFINES EXPORT-RECORD-DATA)
Card number identifier
Account identifier associated with the card (USAGE COMP)
Card Verification Value security code (USAGE COMP)
Name embossed on the physical card
Card expiration date
Card active status indicator
Reserved placeholder field used for data structure alignment, padding, or holding constant values
